04:13.050 --> 04:20.320
           [Applause]

04:20.420 --> 04:27.930
           [Applause]

04:28.030 --> 04:29.730
     Sophia, she has a gift.

04:29.830 --> 04:31.100
      You must be so proud.

04:31.200 --> 04:32.930
    We are, thank you Hannah.

04:33.030 --> 04:36.270
    It's my pleasure to teach
    a student so passionate.

04:36.370 --> 04:38.170
          She loves it.

04:38.270 --> 04:39.140
  You know, we don't even have
     to ask her to rehearse.

04:39.240 --> 04:41.440
          I understand.

04:41.540 --> 04:44.980
  Balance for all of us is key,
              yes?

04:45.080 --> 04:46.750
              Yeah.

04:46.850 --> 04:50.450
      Gifted children, they
  sometimes isolate themselves,

04:50.550 --> 04:52.290
   and if you are busy parents

04:52.390 --> 04:54.450
       sometimes you don't
         see the signs.

04:54.560 --> 04:55.990
       Sophia is fine, she
      has lots of friends.

04:56.090 --> 04:57.620
            She does.

04:57.730 --> 05:00.590
   She has her girls at church
       and her youth group

05:00.700 --> 05:04.100
   and she's always been very
mature, isn't that right, Dylan?

05:04.200 --> 05:06.030
        Yeah, our Sophia
        was born mature.

05:06.130 --> 05:07.070
          She's great.

05:07.170 --> 05:08.070
        Congratulations.

05:08.170 --> 05:09.370
           Thank you.

05:11.370 --> 05:13.370
         Great teacher.

05:13.470 --> 05:14.340
  A little judgmental, though.

05:14.440 --> 05:15.310
       Um, she meant well.

05:15.410 --> 05:16.810
       She meant well, ok?

05:16.910 --> 05:17.940
              Hey!

05:18.050 --> 05:20.850
 Oh, honey, I'm so proud of you!

05:20.950 --> 05:21.920
             Thanks.

05:22.020 --> 05:22.850
          Thanks, mom.

05:22.950 --> 05:24.320
              Yeah.

05:24.420 --> 05:25.420
    How about we go for some
           ice cream?

05:25.520 --> 05:26.990
               Ok.

