07:23.700 --> 07:29.380
    in Shakespeare's Othello.

07:29.480 --> 07:31.010
   Does anyone have any other
   themes that they would like

07:31.110 --> 07:33.050
    to share with the class?

07:33.150 --> 07:37.180
             Anyone?

07:37.290 --> 07:38.020
           [Whistles]

07:38.120 --> 07:40.150
           Mr. Floyd?

07:40.250 --> 07:42.490
     Uh... don't mac on your
        bro's girlfriend?

07:42.590 --> 07:45.290
            [Laughs]

07:45.390 --> 07:47.030
               No.

07:47.130 --> 07:47.830
           Who's that?

07:47.930 --> 07:48.660
         Can I help you?

07:48.760 --> 07:50.500
         Michelle Foley?

07:50.600 --> 07:51.930
  Class began ten minutes ago,
           Miss Foley.

07:52.030 --> 07:53.300
       I know, I'm sorry.

07:53.400 --> 07:54.730
           I got lost.

07:54.840 --> 07:56.200
    Well, don't make a habit
         of being late.

07:56.300 --> 07:57.470
          Find a seat.

08:03.380 --> 08:06.250
      Don't worry, his bark
     is worse than his bite.

08:06.350 --> 08:08.420
           I hope so.

08:08.520 --> 08:09.520
             Sophia.

08:09.620 --> 08:11.690
            Michelle.

08:11.790 --> 08:14.620
   Did I see you playing piano
         before school?

08:14.720 --> 08:16.190
          You saw that?

08:16.290 --> 08:18.560
        You're very good.

08:19.060 --> 08:21.900
      So where do you sit?

08:22.000 --> 08:24.500
        Just by herself.

08:24.600 --> 08:25.630
     Come on, why don't you
        come sit with us?

08:25.730 --> 08:27.400
      We're a lot more fun.

08:27.500 --> 08:31.910
    Aw, that's so sweet, but
    I'm allergic to plastic.

08:35.710 --> 08:37.480
       Mind if I join you?

08:37.580 --> 08:39.679
       Mi casa es su casa.

08:49.120 --> 08:52.260
    So how long have you been
         playing piano?

08:52.360 --> 08:54.090
       Since I was eight.

08:54.200 --> 08:56.730
  My mom had this old keyboard,
   one of those Casio things.

08:56.830 --> 08:58.300
  I used to bang on it all day

08:58.400 --> 09:00.770
 until finally she signed me up
          for lessons.

09:00.870 --> 09:03.240
   So why do you practice here
        and not at home?

09:03.340 --> 09:04.340
          Better piano.

09:04.440 --> 09:05.210
        Better acoustics.

09:05.310 --> 09:07.240
               Oh.

09:07.340 --> 09:08.280
         What about you?

09:08.380 --> 09:09.540
          Do you play?

09:09.640 --> 09:10.640
             I wish.

09:10.750 --> 09:12.350
     I'm actually tone deaf.

09:12.450 --> 09:13.250
               Oh.

09:13.350 --> 09:14.950
              Yeah.

09:15.050 --> 09:16.580
  I had a lot of ear infections
       when I was younger

09:16.680 --> 09:19.520
 so music was never really gonna
          be my thing.

09:19.620 --> 09:20.290
     So where are you from?

09:20.390 --> 09:22.220
             Marion.

09:22.320 --> 09:25.290
       Oh, what brings you
      all the way up here?

09:25.390 --> 09:28.630
    My mom died last year, so
  I'm staying with my grandma.

09:28.730 --> 09:30.260
               Oh.

09:30.360 --> 09:31.430
           I'm sorry.

09:31.530 --> 09:33.870
             Thanks.

09:33.970 --> 09:36.040
 I think the change will be good
             for me.

09:36.140 --> 09:37.600
   Well, it's not so bad here.

09:37.710 --> 09:42.740
  If you stay away from Alison
        and her minions.

09:42.840 --> 09:43.640
           Not so bad?

09:43.740 --> 09:45.550
       Are you kidding me?

09:45.650 --> 09:47.810
  I came from a private school,
 we're talking nuns with rulers.

09:47.920 --> 09:49.420
    Anything would be better
           than that.

09:49.520 --> 09:50.980
   Well, I'm glad you're here.

09:51.090 --> 09:52.490
             Me too.

09:56.420 --> 09:57.760
             Dig in.

10:00.700 --> 10:06.330
      [Schoolyard chatter]

10:06.430 --> 10:08.170
             Sophia!

10:08.270 --> 10:09.500
             Sophia!

10:12.210 --> 10:13.310
      Where are you going?

10:13.410 --> 10:15.410
              Work.

10:15.510 --> 10:17.480
     Do you ever just, like,
             chill?

10:17.580 --> 10:18.750
          I'm too busy.

10:18.850 --> 10:19.710
        That's my point.

10:19.810 --> 10:22.420
       Where do you work?

10:22.520 --> 10:23.380
            My mom's.

10:23.480 --> 10:25.250
       She's an architect.

10:25.350 --> 10:27.490
  I help with files and copying
  stuff and that sort of thing.

10:27.590 --> 10:28.490
        Sounds exciting.

10:28.590 --> 10:30.060
          Electrifying.

10:30.160 --> 10:32.330
       But that's the way
     we like her, isn't it?

10:32.430 --> 10:33.460
           Very funny.

10:33.560 --> 10:34.790
        Who's the newbie?

10:34.900 --> 10:36.400
   Oh, Alex, this is Michelle.

10:36.500 --> 10:37.530
     Michelle, this is Alex.

10:37.630 --> 10:38.500
          He's my uh...

10:38.600 --> 10:39.630
          Study buddy.

10:39.730 --> 10:41.100
      Pleased to meet you.

10:41.200 --> 10:43.100
       Uh, are we cramming
       for Spanish later?

10:43.200 --> 10:45.670
     No puero, I gotta work.

10:45.770 --> 10:47.110
    Then cram alone, I shall.

10:47.210 --> 10:47.770
     It's nice to meet you.

10:47.880 --> 10:51.040
            You too.

10:51.150 --> 10:54.110
        Study buddy, huh?

10:54.220 --> 10:55.750
           Yeah, uh...

10:55.850 --> 10:57.680
     I help him with Spanish
    and he helps me with my--

10:57.790 --> 10:58.790
            Biology?

10:58.890 --> 11:01.250
            No, math.

11:01.360 --> 11:02.960
    I'm just teasing, Sophia.

11:03.060 --> 11:06.390
  But, you do like him, I mean,
      it's pretty obvious.

11:06.490 --> 11:08.360
 I really do have to go though,
    so I'll see you tomorrow?

11:08.460 --> 11:09.930
              Yeah.

11:10.030 --> 11:10.630
     Um, give me your number
       so I can text you.

11:10.730 --> 11:11.830
              Sure.

11:17.510 --> 11:18.070
             Thanks.

11:18.170 --> 11:18.740
              Bye.

11:18.840 --> 11:20.240
              Bye.

11:41.200 --> 11:42.160
            Oh, hey!

11:42.260 --> 11:43.860
              Hey.

11:43.960 --> 11:45.330
 I'm just gonna finish printing
       all the blueprints

11:45.430 --> 11:46.600
    for the Foggerty project.

11:46.700 --> 11:47.800
         Oh, thank you.

11:47.900 --> 11:49.770
 I have not had any time today.

11:53.670 --> 11:55.710
   The model is looking good,
            isn't it?

11:55.810 --> 11:56.580
              Wow.

11:56.680 --> 11:59.650
              Yeah.

11:59.750 --> 12:02.750
           Even a dog.

12:02.850 --> 12:06.790
      Yeah, It's all about
          the details.

12:06.890 --> 12:10.590
   If we get this development
  deal it's gonna be very good

12:10.690 --> 12:12.730
        for the company.

12:12.830 --> 12:14.630
       Not to mention us.

12:19.100 --> 12:20.500
   Your father and I are gonna
     watch a movie tonight,

12:20.600 --> 12:23.500
       are you interested?

12:23.600 --> 12:25.870
  Eh, after I finish here I've
    got some homework to do.

12:25.970 --> 12:28.840
   Oh, honey, you do not have
         to do all that.

12:28.940 --> 12:30.810
         Mom, I want to.

12:30.910 --> 12:33.480
       I know the pressure
          you're under.

12:33.580 --> 12:37.580
  I'll tell you what, I am very
       lucky to have you.

12:37.690 --> 12:39.590
    So how was school today?

12:39.690 --> 12:41.820
           The usual.

12:41.920 --> 12:44.190
      Oh, I met a new girl.

12:44.290 --> 12:45.630
            Oh yeah?

12:45.730 --> 12:47.290
        What's her name?

12:47.390 --> 12:48.960
         Michelle Foley.

12:49.060 --> 12:50.800
  I thought maybe I'd show her
      around this weekend.

12:50.900 --> 12:52.670
      That should be nice.

12:54.870 --> 13:00.340
      [Text message alert]

13:03.610 --> 13:05.040
       Speak of the devil.

13:47.820 --> 14:01.270
          [Piano music]

14:01.370 --> 14:10.240
          [Piano music]

14:10.340 --> 14:12.880
        The tempo is off
       and you are stiff.

14:12.980 --> 14:14.680
      Don't read the notes,
          don't think.

14:14.780 --> 14:16.550
         Feel the music.

14:16.650 --> 14:18.590
            Breathe.

14:18.690 --> 14:20.420
             Again.

14:23.020 --> 14:31.600
          [Piano music]

14:31.700 --> 14:32.670
             Bravo.

14:32.770 --> 14:34.270
           Very good.

14:34.370 --> 14:36.270
       You have two weeks
       before competition.

14:36.370 --> 14:37.670
    It's time to get serious.

14:37.770 --> 14:39.540
           Yes, ma'am.

14:39.640 --> 14:43.640
Also, this is a rehearsal space,
        not socializing.

14:43.740 --> 14:44.980
      She's just watching.

14:45.080 --> 14:47.950
     She's distracting you.

14:48.050 --> 14:49.950
     I'll see you tomorrow.

14:58.030 --> 15:00.330
   She's quite something, huh?

15:00.430 --> 15:03.500
  My parents aren't paying her
  for her charming personality.

15:03.600 --> 15:06.130
    What competition are you
         practicing for?

15:06.230 --> 15:08.640
Well, every year the Harold King
        Foundation awards

15:08.740 --> 15:11.670
       a full scholarship
   to an exceptional musician.

15:11.770 --> 15:14.410
  It can be used for any school
       you're accepted to.

15:14.510 --> 15:16.080
  Have you picked one out yet?

15:16.180 --> 15:17.580
           Juilliard.

15:17.680 --> 15:18.880
              Wow.

15:18.980 --> 15:21.180
       All the way across
          the country.

15:21.280 --> 15:24.620
 Yeah, and it's super expensive,
   so I need that scholarship.

15:24.720 --> 15:26.890
    Well, you're really good.

15:26.990 --> 15:28.350
  They have to give it to you.

15:28.460 --> 15:29.320
             Thanks.

15:29.420 --> 15:31.420
     I have to get to class.

15:31.530 --> 15:32.830
             See ya.

15:43.840 --> 15:52.010
      [Piano playing badly]

15:52.110 --> 15:59.450
      [Piano playing badly]

15:59.550 --> 16:01.120
              Argh!

16:16.700 --> 16:20.640
            [Giggles]

17:09.460 --> 17:10.589
              Wow.

17:10.690 --> 17:11.990
  Nice flowers, Mrs. Daverston.

17:12.089 --> 17:13.730
         Oh, thank you.

17:13.829 --> 17:14.790
           Thank you.

17:14.900 --> 17:15.930
  You must be Sophia's friend.

17:16.030 --> 17:18.160
            Michelle.

17:18.270 --> 17:20.069
    I'm surprised you do your
         own gardening.

17:20.170 --> 17:22.140
    Sophia says you're a very
         busy architect.

17:22.240 --> 17:24.839
  You know, it comes in waves.

17:24.940 --> 17:28.640
     Feel free to go inside,
      I'm sure Sophia's up.

17:28.740 --> 17:29.510
        Nice to meet you.

17:29.610 --> 17:31.040
            You, too.

17:33.780 --> 17:34.910
             Sophia?

17:35.020 --> 17:35.880
         Rise and shine.

17:35.980 --> 17:37.320
        Michelle is here.

17:42.620 --> 17:43.560
     So where are you from,
            Michelle?

17:43.660 --> 17:45.590
             Marion.

17:45.690 --> 17:46.760
             Really?

17:46.860 --> 17:48.690
    Isn't that where Bethany
            teaches?

17:48.800 --> 17:49.760
            Yes, yes.

17:49.860 --> 17:51.760
   One of my college friends.

17:51.870 --> 17:54.800
     So have you had one of
   Mrs. Williamson's classes?

17:54.900 --> 17:56.400
              Hey!

17:56.500 --> 17:59.010
 You never told me your parents
        were so awesome.

17:59.110 --> 18:00.710
       What are you doing?

18:00.810 --> 18:02.110
Just looking at some old photos.

18:02.210 --> 18:03.180
     You don't mind, do you?

18:03.280 --> 18:05.780
       No, of course not.

18:05.880 --> 18:07.950
      Aw, this is adorable!

18:08.050 --> 18:09.550
   Do you mind if I borrow it?

18:09.650 --> 18:10.580
              Yeah.

18:10.680 --> 18:12.090
   I don't- I don't think so.

18:12.190 --> 18:12.950
        You can keep it.

18:13.050 --> 18:14.650
        It's just a copy.

18:14.760 --> 18:15.390
             Really?

18:15.490 --> 18:16.760
           Yeah. Here.

18:16.860 --> 18:18.320
             Thanks.

18:21.160 --> 18:21.860
             Ready?

18:21.960 --> 18:23.530
            You bet.

18:23.630 --> 18:25.700
    It was nice to meet you,
     Mr. and Mrs. Daverston.

18:25.800 --> 18:27.430
  It was nice to meet you, too.

18:28.700 --> 18:31.100
    I'll be back in an hour.

18:40.310 --> 18:43.880
     Where'd she get a phone
           like that?

18:43.980 --> 18:46.890
          What's wrong?

18:46.990 --> 18:49.220
     There's just something
           about her.

18:49.320 --> 18:50.690
     Because she didn't know
        who Bethany was?

18:50.790 --> 18:52.160
   The school is not that big.

18:52.260 --> 18:56.160
     It was like she didn't
         even know her.

18:56.260 --> 18:58.100
     Sophia's got a friend.

18:58.200 --> 18:59.900
         Just let it go.

19:00.000 --> 19:01.830
               Ok?

19:10.640 --> 19:12.380
  Your parents are so talented.

19:12.480 --> 19:14.050
       Did your mom design
           your house?

19:14.150 --> 19:15.680
      Yeah, she designed it
          from scratch.

19:15.780 --> 19:16.650
              Cool.

19:16.750 --> 19:17.950
    You ever bring Alex here?

19:18.050 --> 19:19.520
               No.

19:19.620 --> 19:20.620
            Why not?

19:20.720 --> 19:21.850
  You guys make a cute couple.

19:21.960 --> 19:22.620
           We're not.

19:22.720 --> 19:23.690
           We're just-

19:23.790 --> 19:25.160
         Study buddies,
            I heard.

19:25.260 --> 19:27.090
   But I see the way he looks
             at you.

19:27.190 --> 19:27.890
           It's like-

19:28.000 --> 19:28.830
           Like what?

19:28.930 --> 19:31.130
    Like more than homework.

19:31.230 --> 19:32.870
          I don't know.

19:32.970 --> 19:34.270
      If there's one thing
          I've learned,

19:34.370 --> 19:35.770
    you've gotta move quickly
          in this world

19:35.870 --> 19:37.040
      because if you don't
       someone else will.

19:37.140 --> 19:38.840
     You've gotta take over.

19:38.940 --> 19:41.140
 Just to clarify, we are talking
       about Alex, right?

19:41.240 --> 19:42.740
         Guys, whatever.

19:42.840 --> 19:45.580
     But I was talking about
     the music scholarship.

19:45.680 --> 19:47.280
   Oh, Hannah would love you.

19:50.320 --> 19:51.820
              Eww.

19:51.920 --> 19:53.350
              What?

19:53.450 --> 19:55.790
   I leaned against that fence
        when I was four.

19:55.890 --> 19:56.960
               So?

19:57.060 --> 19:58.890
        There was a nest
        of baby spiders.

19:58.990 --> 20:00.260
          You serious?

20:00.360 --> 20:01.830
You got covered in baby spiders?

20:01.930 --> 20:03.500
            Stop it!

20:03.600 --> 20:05.200
  I should have gotten therapy,
       it was disturbing.

20:05.300 --> 20:06.730
     Ok, I'll tell you what.

20:06.830 --> 20:08.330
       Let's have a race.

20:08.440 --> 20:10.000
   Pretend we're being chased
       by a giant spider.

20:10.100 --> 20:11.900
    Whoever gets there first
     lives to tell the tale.

20:12.010 --> 20:12.810
        Are you serious?

20:12.910 --> 20:13.840
           So serious.

20:13.940 --> 20:15.010
            Michelle!

20:15.110 --> 20:15.840
        Come on, Sophia!

20:15.940 --> 20:17.210
              Stop!

20:17.310 --> 20:17.980
    I know you can run faster
           than that!

20:18.080 --> 20:19.880
           No, I can't

20:19.980 --> 20:21.750
    That was a good workout.

20:21.850 --> 20:23.880
    Wow, this is really cool.

20:23.980 --> 20:25.550
             Thanks.

20:25.650 --> 20:26.790
 I'm gonna grab a quick shower.

20:26.890 --> 20:27.950
       I'll just be a sec.

20:28.060 --> 20:29.060
           No problem.

20:29.160 --> 20:30.160
   Make yourself comfortable.

20:30.260 --> 20:32.160
       Mi casa es su casa.

20:37.800 --> 20:38.730
    I love the bohemian vibe.

20:38.830 --> 20:40.370
             Thanks.

20:40.470 --> 20:42.570
     I got a lot of stuff in
     the consignment shops.

20:45.140 --> 20:50.240
        [Shower running]

22:21.400 --> 22:22.500
          [Door opens]

22:26.010 --> 22:28.110
   My father gave that to me.

22:28.210 --> 22:29.980
             Sorry.

22:30.080 --> 22:31.310
        The box was open.

22:31.410 --> 22:33.350
         It's beautiful.

22:33.450 --> 22:35.510
       He bought it for me
      for my 13th birthday.

22:35.620 --> 22:39.150
  He said "Every grown up girl
   needs a grown up necklace".

22:39.250 --> 22:40.420
     I'd love to borrow it.

22:40.520 --> 22:41.890
            Sometime.

22:41.990 --> 22:44.860
              Sure.

22:44.960 --> 22:46.430
     So your parents are ok
         with all this?

22:46.530 --> 22:47.460
            Why not?

22:47.560 --> 22:49.430
          It's my room.

22:49.530 --> 22:53.670
         I love vintage.

22:53.770 --> 22:57.700
    My mom says that my style
       is older than her.

22:57.800 --> 22:59.740
    I'd be happy to help you
        re-do your room.

22:59.840 --> 23:02.010
   I could come over sometime.

23:02.110 --> 23:02.980
              Sure.

23:03.080 --> 23:04.740
            Sometime.

23:04.850 --> 23:07.050
   You never told me where you
   and your grandmother live.

23:07.150 --> 23:09.650
   You know, I should actually
           get going.

23:09.750 --> 23:11.350
   She gets upset if I'm away
          for too long.

23:11.450 --> 23:12.520
     You know grandparents.

23:12.620 --> 23:14.190
  Michelle this, Michelle that.

23:14.290 --> 23:15.720
              Sure.

23:15.820 --> 23:17.360
   Anyways, thanks for having
            me over.

23:17.460 --> 23:19.160
    Yeah, thanks for coming.

23:20.990 --> 23:21.730
       See you on Monday.

23:21.830 --> 23:23.330
            See you.

23:42.150 --> 23:52.560
 [Piano playing]

23:52.660 --> 23:55.160
    Well, your tempo is still
          a little off.

23:55.260 --> 23:56.760
      I thought it was ok.

23:56.860 --> 23:59.800
     It needs to be perfect.

23:59.900 --> 24:01.670
    I'll work on it some more
     before the competition.

24:01.770 --> 24:03.500
            You must.

24:09.640 --> 24:11.440
              Hey.

24:11.550 --> 24:13.410
        She doesn't know
    what she's talking about.

24:13.510 --> 24:14.410
         You're amazing.

24:14.510 --> 24:15.750
             Thanks.

24:15.850 --> 24:17.250
         See you later.

24:17.350 --> 24:18.920
              Bye.

24:22.590 --> 24:24.890
      I thought I told you
           about her.

24:24.990 --> 24:26.790
    She's not distracting me.

24:26.890 --> 24:28.860
    You only have one chance.

24:28.960 --> 24:32.730
        You cannot afford
        any distractions.

24:32.830 --> 24:34.600
     I don't want to see her
          here anymore.

24:34.700 --> 24:36.600
          Are we clear?

24:36.700 --> 24:38.570
       Yeah, that's fine.

24:38.670 --> 24:40.940
               Ok.

25:09.600 --> 25:13.170
         [Engine fails]

25:13.270 --> 25:14.810
              What?

25:33.430 --> 25:33.990
          [Slams hood]

25:34.090 --> 25:35.660
             [Gasps]

25:35.760 --> 25:37.300
   Oh, you should be careful,

25:37.400 --> 25:38.960
       these old cars are
         so unreliable!

25:39.070 --> 25:40.200
     What is wrong with you?

25:40.300 --> 25:41.730
       You might get hurt,

25:41.840 --> 25:44.240
   and that might put a damper
        on your teaching.

25:44.340 --> 25:45.370
      I'm going to call...

25:45.470 --> 25:48.170
   I'm going to call security.

25:48.280 --> 25:50.710
   I'm sure the police will be
         very interested

25:50.810 --> 25:52.710
to find out what kind of private
   lessons you've been giving

25:52.810 --> 25:54.410
       in public schools.

25:54.510 --> 25:55.610
      How did you get this?

25:58.750 --> 26:02.620
  Don't ever tell me who I can
   and can't be friends with.

26:16.940 --> 26:30.220
                ♪

26:30.320 --> 26:43.200
                ♪

26:43.300 --> 26:56.210
                ♪

26:56.310 --> 27:09.220
                ♪

27:09.320 --> 27:22.230
                ♪

27:22.340 --> 27:35.250
                ♪

27:35.350 --> 27:48.260
                ♪

27:48.360 --> 28:01.270
                ♪

28:01.370 --> 28:14.290
                ♪

28:14.390 --> 28:25.200
                ♪

28:25.300 --> 28:28.400
     So they ask me to go on
        this field trip.

28:28.500 --> 28:31.440
   I'd rather gargle bees than
    go on another field trip.

28:31.540 --> 28:33.710
      Honestly, these kids.

28:33.810 --> 28:34.770
          I don't know.

28:34.870 --> 28:36.240
   They are the future, right?

28:36.340 --> 28:38.640
      I mean, I want to get
         them motivated.

28:38.750 --> 28:40.980
     They're so complacent.

28:41.080 --> 28:43.720
       I don't know, maybe
      a pop quiz tomorrow?

28:43.820 --> 28:46.920
  See if any of them have been
        paying attention.

28:56.730 --> 28:57.530
              Hey.

28:57.630 --> 28:59.060
           What's up?

28:59.170 --> 29:01.200
      I was just thinking.

29:01.300 --> 29:03.300
     There's not much to do
          in this town.

29:03.400 --> 29:04.840
     Well, what do you want
             to do?

29:04.940 --> 29:05.800
          I don't know.

29:05.910 --> 29:08.010
      Something different.

29:08.110 --> 29:09.640
   What're you doing tonight?

29:09.740 --> 29:10.980
     I don't know, homework.

29:11.080 --> 29:12.850
            Studying.

29:12.950 --> 29:15.150
              Why?

29:15.250 --> 29:16.820
   You want to have some fun?

29:20.620 --> 29:28.190
          [Dance music]
               ♪♪

29:28.290 --> 29:35.430
          [Dance music]
               ♪♪

29:35.540 --> 29:37.200
     What are we doing here?

29:37.300 --> 29:38.900
        I told you, it's
        a college party.

29:39.010 --> 29:41.510
        We're gonna have
          a little fun.

29:41.610 --> 29:43.540
 But we're high school students.

29:43.640 --> 29:45.240
 Don't worry, I got it covered.

29:47.810 --> 29:48.680
             There.

29:48.780 --> 29:49.920
     Now let's check it out.

29:50.020 --> 29:53.620
              [♪♪]

29:53.720 --> 29:55.890
       Welcome to college.

29:55.990 --> 29:57.620
           Thank you.

29:57.720 --> 30:10.940
              [♪♪]

30:11.040 --> 30:23.950
              [♪♪]

30:24.050 --> 30:38.200
              [♪♪]

30:49.510 --> 30:51.640
             You ok?

30:51.740 --> 30:52.680
         Ok, everybody.

30:52.780 --> 30:54.250
        Did you miss me?

30:54.350 --> 30:57.020
    Just in case you didn't,
    here's some No. 2 pencils

30:57.120 --> 30:59.850
   and everyone's favourite...

30:59.950 --> 31:00.750
           a pop quiz.

31:00.850 --> 31:01.790
          That's right.

31:01.890 --> 31:03.120
          [Class groans]

31:03.220 --> 31:05.020
  Oh, groan, groan, sigh, sigh.

31:05.120 --> 31:07.790
          There you go.

31:07.890 --> 31:12.930
   Ok, take one, pass it along.

31:13.030 --> 31:14.500
       Here's some for you.

31:20.740 --> 31:22.840
   Make sure everyone gets one.

31:22.940 --> 31:24.380
        Did everyone get-

31:24.480 --> 31:25.540
        oh, here, we need
          a pencil here.

31:25.650 --> 31:26.410
    Let's grab another pencil.

31:26.510 --> 31:27.380
          Pass one down.

31:27.480 --> 31:30.620
            Thank you.

31:30.720 --> 31:31.780
              Enjoy.

31:31.890 --> 31:33.550
      It was only one quiz.

31:33.650 --> 31:35.990
    I got Cassio and Rodrigo
            confused.

31:36.090 --> 31:37.420
   I need an A in that class.

31:37.520 --> 31:42.290
       If I don't get one
       my GPA is screwed.

31:42.400 --> 31:44.660
      How could he do that?

31:44.760 --> 31:46.630
   How was I supposed to know
 there was gonna be a pop quiz?

31:46.730 --> 31:49.170
    I should have never gone.

31:49.270 --> 31:51.000
       You know my family
     was waiting up for me?

31:51.100 --> 31:52.910
   They knew something was up.

31:53.010 --> 31:54.770
      What'd you tell them?

31:54.870 --> 31:56.610
         Food poisoning.

31:56.710 --> 31:57.610
           [Snickers]

31:57.710 --> 31:59.910
         It's not funny.

32:00.010 --> 32:02.010
 Admit it, you had a good time.

32:02.120 --> 32:04.380
         This isn't me.

32:04.480 --> 32:06.850
     I've never, ever missed
        a piano practice.

32:06.950 --> 32:08.320
              Ever.

32:08.420 --> 32:10.460
     And I need a good grade
          on that test.

32:10.560 --> 32:12.690
   Don't worry, I'll take care
             of it.

32:12.790 --> 32:14.730
              How?

32:14.830 --> 32:16.600
     Just let me handle it.

32:16.700 --> 32:18.060
            Come on.

32:30.880 --> 32:37.050
           [Whistling]

32:37.150 --> 32:44.690
           [Whistling]

32:44.790 --> 32:47.460
           Mr. Clarke?

32:47.560 --> 32:49.360
         Uh, Miss Foley.

32:49.460 --> 32:52.800
      Sorry, I didn't mean
        to make you jump.

32:52.900 --> 32:55.000
     What are you doing here
            so late?

32:55.100 --> 32:56.840
     Repetitions at the gym.

32:56.940 --> 32:58.700
               Ah.

32:58.810 --> 33:01.810
  I was just leaving, but then
  I realized I had a question.

33:01.910 --> 33:03.740
     And what would that be,
           Miss Foley?

33:03.840 --> 33:06.780
        Call me Michelle.

33:06.880 --> 33:09.950
          Ok, Michelle.

33:10.050 --> 33:12.620
            Ask away.

33:12.720 --> 33:16.190
     Well, English has never
      really been my thing

33:16.290 --> 33:21.730
and I was wondering if you could
          help me out.

33:21.830 --> 33:24.860
          In what way?

33:24.960 --> 33:28.000
     You know, extra credit.

33:28.100 --> 33:31.640
    Uh, Miss Foley, I don't-

33:31.740 --> 33:32.600
            Michelle.

33:32.710 --> 33:35.110
            Michelle.

33:35.210 --> 33:37.040
I don't think that this is uh...

33:37.140 --> 33:38.810
    Oh, it's nothing special.

33:38.910 --> 33:42.950
     Just a little tutoring
          after school.

33:43.050 --> 33:44.950
      A little one-on-one.

33:47.620 --> 33:48.550
             I um...

33:48.650 --> 33:54.790
     I don't normally tutor.

33:54.890 --> 33:56.900
              So...

33:57.000 --> 33:59.330
         That's too bad.

33:59.430 --> 34:02.500
  I was kind of looking forward
             to it.

34:02.600 --> 34:05.570
           I said I...

34:05.670 --> 34:07.810
     I don't normally tutor.

34:13.610 --> 34:15.050
        I didn't say no.

34:15.150 --> 34:16.820
              Yeah?

34:21.949 --> 34:22.750
           Mr. Clarke!

34:22.860 --> 34:24.760
             [Slap]

34:24.860 --> 34:26.730
      I don't know what you
   thought I was insinuating!

34:26.830 --> 34:27.830
             Oh, no!

34:27.929 --> 34:28.889
             I- I...

34:29.000 --> 34:30.330
         I um... no, I-

34:30.429 --> 34:31.600
       I am not that type
          of girl, I...

34:31.699 --> 34:32.530
             Oh, I-

34:32.630 --> 34:33.600
              I...

34:33.699 --> 34:35.170
            oh geez.

34:35.270 --> 34:36.600
     Look, it was just a big
      misunderstanding, I-

34:36.699 --> 34:37.500
            I should-

34:37.600 --> 34:38.940
          Miss Foley...

34:39.040 --> 34:39.940
       I should report you
          to Mr. Owens.

34:40.040 --> 34:40.969
        Wait, wait, wait!

34:41.070 --> 34:41.810
         Please, no, no.

34:41.909 --> 34:43.639
        I would never...

34:43.739 --> 34:47.449
  I would never have done that
  unless I thought that you...

34:47.550 --> 34:48.080
             oh god.

34:48.179 --> 34:49.750
            Ok, um...

34:49.850 --> 34:55.949
      Well, I guess I could
     just keep it to myself.

34:56.060 --> 34:58.120
  It was kind of embarrassing.

35:00.960 --> 35:02.830
      Yes, yes, of course.

35:02.930 --> 35:04.200
           Of course.

35:04.300 --> 35:07.070
       No one, no one has
         to know about-

35:07.170 --> 35:08.900
             Wrong.

35:09.000 --> 35:14.810
 In that case I guess I won't be
 needing any tutoring after all.

35:14.910 --> 35:19.580
             Will I?

35:19.680 --> 35:21.650
               No.

35:24.050 --> 35:26.320
        See you in class.

36:32.350 --> 36:34.590
         Michelle, wait.

36:34.690 --> 36:35.720
       How did you do it?

36:35.820 --> 36:37.160
            Do what?

36:37.260 --> 36:38.220
            The test.

36:38.320 --> 36:39.660
          I bombed it.

36:39.760 --> 36:41.590
       Looks like you got
        an A plus to me.

36:41.690 --> 36:42.630
           Seriously.

36:42.730 --> 36:44.660
        How'd you do it?

36:44.760 --> 36:45.800
         Does it matter?

36:45.900 --> 36:47.730
I said I'd handle it, and I did.

36:47.830 --> 36:49.370
           Thank you.

36:49.470 --> 36:51.000
       Really, thank you.

36:51.100 --> 36:52.770
  That's what friends are for.

36:52.870 --> 36:55.110
  Let's celebrate, go shopping
          after school.

36:55.210 --> 36:58.340
  Ooh, I told Alex that I would
 help him study this afternoon.

36:58.440 --> 36:59.080
             Oh, ok.

36:59.180 --> 36:59.980
          Dinner then?

37:00.080 --> 37:01.150
       Maybe around seven?

37:01.250 --> 37:02.280
 Yeah, I guess I could do that.

37:02.380 --> 37:03.220
              Cool.

37:03.320 --> 37:03.850
    I'll wait for your text.

37:03.950 --> 37:04.480
              Sure.

37:04.580 --> 37:05.780
               Ok.

37:08.890 --> 37:10.720
   Aqui. It's a hard K sound.

37:10.820 --> 37:11.620
              Aqui.

37:11.720 --> 37:15.690
              Qui.

37:15.800 --> 37:18.760
        Es usted de aqui.

37:18.860 --> 37:22.230
        Es usted de aqui.

37:22.340 --> 37:23.770
    Are you from around here?

37:32.980 --> 37:35.980
       Why do you help me?

37:36.080 --> 37:38.020
        What do you mean?

37:38.120 --> 37:39.780
 I think we have a better chance

37:39.890 --> 37:42.720
 of Earth being hit by a meteor
 than me ever mastering Spanish.

37:42.820 --> 37:45.590
      Hey, I like my planet
         the way it is.

37:45.690 --> 37:46.560
         Don't jinx it.

37:46.660 --> 37:47.790
           Seriously.

37:50.730 --> 37:53.430
    I don't know, I guess...

37:53.530 --> 37:54.900
     you know, I needed help
            with math

37:55.000 --> 37:57.900
      and I thought it was
          a good deal.

37:58.000 --> 37:59.640
              Why?

37:59.740 --> 38:02.640
         Just wondering.

38:02.740 --> 38:04.610
              Yeah?

38:04.710 --> 38:06.480
              Yeah.

38:27.800 --> 38:30.070
    I think our study session
            is over.

38:30.170 --> 38:32.640
              Yeah.

38:32.740 --> 38:34.740
           I guess so.

38:58.800 --> 38:59.630
I'll see you at school tomorrow?

38:59.730 --> 39:01.800
              Sure.

39:01.900 --> 39:03.440
          Hey, thanks.

39:03.540 --> 39:04.800
       For understanding.

39:04.900 --> 39:05.970
             Course.

39:06.070 --> 39:07.770
        See you tomorrow.

39:15.480 --> 39:18.550
    What are you doing here?

39:18.650 --> 39:19.680
       We were gonna meet.

39:19.790 --> 39:21.490
            Remember?

39:21.590 --> 39:24.520
     I waited for your call.

39:24.620 --> 39:25.920
        It's only eight.

39:26.030 --> 39:28.630
      We were going to meet
            at 7:00.

39:28.730 --> 39:30.660
    Oh, Michelle, I'm sorry.

39:30.760 --> 39:31.600
            I forgot.

39:31.700 --> 39:34.530
       Of course you did.

39:34.630 --> 39:36.370
  What's that supposed to mean?

39:36.470 --> 39:38.740
It means you can't stop thinking
   about yourself long enough

39:38.840 --> 39:42.570
       to consider someone
        else's feelings!

39:42.680 --> 39:44.810
  It was a mistake, I'm sorry.

39:44.910 --> 39:47.180
    After what I did for you?

39:47.280 --> 39:52.120
      You would have failed
 that test if it wasn't for me.

39:52.220 --> 39:54.720
   I thought we were friends.

39:54.820 --> 39:56.420
       I said I was sorry.

39:56.520 --> 39:57.790
     I don't know what else
       you want me to say.

39:57.890 --> 40:00.460
         Just... don't.

40:03.830 --> 40:05.960
            Michelle!

40:14.270 --> 40:23.620
          [Phone rings]

40:51.910 --> 40:54.780
        The presentation
        is in four days.

40:54.880 --> 40:58.850
     That took me two months
            to build.

40:58.950 --> 41:00.850
    Do you have any idea who
  would do something like this?

41:06.060 --> 41:08.160
      I'm going to need you
    to conduct an inventory,

41:08.260 --> 41:10.030
  give us a list of everything
         that's missing.

41:16.340 --> 41:18.170
 Ma'am, can I get you something?

41:18.270 --> 41:20.210
           Are you ok?

41:23.940 --> 41:25.880
         No, I'm not ok.

41:34.850 --> 41:48.430
          [party music]
               ♪♪

41:48.530 --> 42:00.280
          [party music]
               ♪♪

42:00.380 --> 42:07.390
          [party music]
               ♪♪

42:14.330 --> 42:15.730
          [Piano music]

42:15.830 --> 42:16.560
          Hey, Sophia.

42:19.570 --> 42:20.270
            Michelle.

42:23.070 --> 42:26.910
        Something wrong?

42:27.010 --> 42:31.210
    Um... someone broke into
   my mom's office last night.

42:31.310 --> 42:32.680
               Oh.

42:32.780 --> 42:36.010
        Is everything ok?

42:36.120 --> 42:37.780
          I'm not sure.

42:37.880 --> 42:38.820
          Hey, I uh...

42:38.920 --> 42:40.850
     I wanted to apologize.

42:40.950 --> 42:45.590
    I'm sorry, I overreacted
           selfishly.

42:45.690 --> 42:47.860
I didn't think of your feelings.

42:47.960 --> 42:50.160
   I hope you can forgive me.

42:50.260 --> 42:52.830
       What do you think?

42:52.930 --> 42:56.370
   Oh, I hope you don't mind.

42:56.470 --> 42:58.900
       You told me I could
          borrow them.

42:59.000 --> 43:02.570
     You're just so stylish
        and interesting,

43:02.680 --> 43:05.110
 I thought I'd follow your lead.

43:05.210 --> 43:08.980
After all, best friends forever,
             right?

43:09.080 --> 43:11.780
         [Clears throat]

43:11.880 --> 43:14.850
      Ready for rehearsal,
             Sophia?

43:14.950 --> 43:16.320
              Yes.

43:23.130 --> 43:24.860
     Try to break everything
         from your mind

43:24.960 --> 43:27.870
      except for the music.

43:27.970 --> 43:32.900
            [ticking]

43:33.010 --> 43:42.750
         [Piano playing]

43:42.850 --> 43:45.650
           I'm sorry.

43:45.750 --> 43:47.890
            I can't.

43:47.990 --> 43:49.320
              Hey.

43:49.420 --> 43:51.260
    Tell you what, let me get
        out of your hair.

43:51.360 --> 43:54.060
     I'll see you in class.

43:54.160 --> 43:56.060
        Goodbye, Hannah.

44:23.060 --> 44:25.190
     Looks like someone got
    their own little mini-me.

44:25.290 --> 44:26.920
            How cute.

44:27.030 --> 44:28.130
             Alison.

44:28.230 --> 44:31.460
        To what do I owe
          the pleasure?

44:31.560 --> 44:34.130
     As much as it pains me,

44:34.230 --> 44:35.530
     in the interest of what
        I'll classify as

44:35.630 --> 44:36.930
      "community outreach",

44:37.040 --> 44:38.000
  I was wondering if you'd like
            to attend

44:38.100 --> 44:39.940
 a little barbecue after school.

44:40.040 --> 44:41.740
               Oh.

44:41.840 --> 44:44.040
     As appreciative as I am
 for that heartfelt invitation,

44:44.140 --> 44:46.110
     I'm gonna have to pass.

44:46.210 --> 44:47.550
   Someone broke into my mom's
        office last night

44:47.650 --> 44:50.010
and I have to help after school.

44:50.120 --> 44:51.420
        Oh, that's right.

44:51.520 --> 44:53.180
 You little office worker, you.

44:53.290 --> 44:54.220
              Yeah.

44:54.320 --> 44:55.820
    Not all of us can afford

44:55.920 --> 44:59.460
      to pimp ourselves out
     on daddy's trust-fund.

44:59.560 --> 45:02.060
     Well, maybe I'll invite
          Twiddle Dee.

45:02.160 --> 45:05.200
      She has better legs.

45:05.300 --> 45:07.100
            Have fun.

45:07.200 --> 45:08.670
             See ya.

45:10.440 --> 45:12.140
     Don't hold your breath.

45:26.390 --> 45:27.750
    Ok, well we've cleaned up
        the worst of it,

45:27.850 --> 45:30.250
I think we should call it a day.

45:30.360 --> 45:32.760
    Not yet, I'm almost done
        with these files.

45:32.860 --> 45:34.690
        Oh, Sophia honey,
         that can wait.

45:34.790 --> 45:37.560
  You should be out in the sun
           having fun.

45:37.660 --> 45:38.630
       No mom, you should.

45:38.730 --> 45:41.600
         I'll finish up.

45:41.700 --> 45:43.000
    Sophia, honey, come here.

45:43.100 --> 45:44.200
            Sit down.

45:50.780 --> 45:53.010
  Honey, I'm worried about you.

45:53.110 --> 45:53.680
              What?

45:53.780 --> 45:55.880
              Why?

45:55.980 --> 46:00.180
    Because you're a teenager
  and you should be having fun,

46:00.290 --> 46:01.050
            you know?

46:01.150 --> 46:02.450
       With your friends.

46:02.550 --> 46:03.220
     You should be shopping,
        going to movies,

46:03.320 --> 46:04.220
        going to parties.

46:04.320 --> 46:05.490
       Having a good time.

46:05.590 --> 46:08.460
           I have fun.

46:08.560 --> 46:10.930
 Where are you going with this?

46:11.030 --> 46:14.170
 It's just, you know, your whole
   life revolves around school

46:14.270 --> 46:18.500
        and then practice
         and then work.

46:18.600 --> 46:23.940
        Mom, I'm healthy
         and I'm happy.

46:24.040 --> 46:26.880
  And I promise on my way home
   I will get my head shaved,

46:26.980 --> 46:32.250
      my nose pierced, and
     I'm thinking a tattoo.

46:32.350 --> 46:34.320
           How's that?

46:34.420 --> 46:36.290
           I love you.

46:36.390 --> 46:38.260
      I love you too, mom.

46:39.460 --> 46:41.730
               Ok.

46:41.830 --> 46:44.060
     So you know how to work
      the new alarm system?

46:44.160 --> 46:45.530
           I sure do.

46:45.630 --> 46:48.600
    And you'll make it sooner
       rather than later?

46:48.700 --> 46:51.370
       I will. I promise.

46:51.470 --> 46:53.600
         And no tattoo.

47:00.480 --> 47:07.450
      [Text message alert]

47:20.870 --> 47:26.670
          [Party music]

47:26.770 --> 47:34.310
          [Party music]

47:34.410 --> 47:35.350
              Hey.

47:35.450 --> 47:36.510
              Hey.

47:36.620 --> 47:37.820
  What're you doing over here?

47:37.920 --> 47:39.350
   It's not my scene, really.

47:39.450 --> 47:40.650
           Me neither.

47:40.750 --> 47:42.290
      Could have fooled me.

47:42.390 --> 47:42.920
         You look good.

47:43.020 --> 47:43.790
             Thanks.

47:43.890 --> 47:44.820
        You want a drink?

47:44.920 --> 47:46.560
         I don't drink.

47:46.660 --> 47:48.160
    I think I saw some punch.

47:48.260 --> 47:49.160
              Sure.

47:49.260 --> 47:50.800
       I'll be right back.

48:05.910 --> 48:07.380
            Oh, here.

48:07.480 --> 48:09.680
        One non-alcoholic
          fruit punch.

48:09.780 --> 48:11.150
         You really know
          how to party.

48:11.250 --> 48:11.780
             Thanks.

48:11.880 --> 48:13.180
             Cheers.

48:17.890 --> 48:19.390
           It's good.

48:49.250 --> 48:50.920
       You're having fun?

48:51.020 --> 48:52.560
     Are you sure the punch
   didn't have anything in it?

48:52.660 --> 48:54.990
           Yeah. Why?

48:55.090 --> 48:57.500
      I don't know, I feel
         a little funny.

48:57.600 --> 49:00.230
              Aww.

49:00.330 --> 49:01.630
      You want to sit down?

49:01.730 --> 49:03.230
             Maybe.

49:06.610 --> 49:08.170
    Can I make a confession?

49:08.270 --> 49:09.740
              Sure.

49:09.840 --> 49:12.510
  I kind of have a little thing
            for you.

49:12.610 --> 49:13.440
             Really?

49:13.550 --> 49:14.980
              Yeah.

49:15.080 --> 49:20.180
    But I didn't want to get
    in the way, with Sophia.

49:20.290 --> 49:22.250
       I feel bad, though.

49:22.350 --> 49:24.920
   You're just wrapped around
 her little finger, aren't you?

49:25.020 --> 49:26.290
      [Text message alert]

49:26.390 --> 49:27.730
      I think I better go.

49:27.830 --> 49:29.260
              Aww.

49:29.360 --> 49:31.900
          Take it easy.

49:32.000 --> 49:34.700
       I'll tell you what.

49:34.800 --> 49:37.440
         You just relax.

50:12.770 --> 50:14.110
        [Glass crunches]

50:44.570 --> 50:46.340
 Well, look who decided to come.

51:12.660 --> 51:13.660
             Sophia?

51:28.180 --> 51:30.380
        Detective Burke?

51:30.480 --> 51:31.950
               Hi.

51:32.050 --> 51:34.250
 I was just wondering if you had
         any information

51:34.350 --> 51:36.820
        on who might have
        been responsible.

51:36.920 --> 51:39.520
    Like I told your mother,
  we're doing the best we can.

51:39.620 --> 51:41.860
    What if I found something
        that might help?

51:41.960 --> 51:42.690
           Like what?

51:47.270 --> 51:48.970
          What is this?

51:49.070 --> 51:51.140
        I think it's from
       a cell phone case.

51:51.240 --> 51:53.970
   Is there any way you could
            track it?

51:54.070 --> 51:56.410
 Do you know anyone with a cell
      phone case like this?

51:56.510 --> 51:58.240
         Michelle Foley.

51:58.340 --> 52:01.850
   And would she have a motive
   to do something like this?

52:01.950 --> 52:04.180
          I don't know.

52:04.280 --> 52:05.250
             Maybe.

52:05.350 --> 52:07.550
    You don't seem too sure.

52:07.650 --> 52:10.390
      She's a strange girl.

52:11.860 --> 52:12.690
       We'll look into it.

52:12.790 --> 52:13.620
        Can I keep this?

52:13.730 --> 52:14.760
           Sure. Yeah.

52:14.860 --> 52:15.590
             Thanks.

52:15.690 --> 52:17.090
        Have a good one.

52:20.800 --> 52:25.370
         [Phone ringing]

53:16.390 --> 53:18.420
     You can't just pretend
         I don't exist.

53:18.520 --> 53:19.390
            Watch me.

53:19.490 --> 53:20.490
     I need to talk to you.

53:20.590 --> 53:21.690
          Talk to Alex.

53:21.790 --> 53:23.690
   Is that what this is about?

53:23.800 --> 53:25.100
   I thought we were friends!

53:29.800 --> 53:31.370
         I'm not moving!

53:31.470 --> 53:33.340
    Come on, the competition
           is tonight,

53:33.440 --> 53:34.940
      I need to get ready!

53:35.040 --> 53:35.940
  I'm not moving until you get
         out of the car

53:36.040 --> 53:37.310
       and you talk to me!

53:37.410 --> 53:37.980
          I need to go!

53:38.080 --> 53:38.810
            Come on!

53:38.910 --> 53:40.810
          [Honks horn]

53:43.620 --> 53:44.720
            Come on!

53:44.820 --> 53:47.050
          [Honks horn]

53:47.150 --> 53:49.320
          Come on, get
         out of the way!

53:49.420 --> 53:49.990
            Come on!

53:50.090 --> 53:52.260
             Leave-

53:52.360 --> 53:54.290
       You two practicing
         your road rage?

54:28.060 --> 54:33.300
         [Violin music]

54:33.400 --> 54:35.600
       You look beautiful.

54:35.700 --> 54:38.800
     How are you holding up?

54:38.900 --> 54:41.070
  Bad case of the butterflies.

54:41.170 --> 54:43.940
    Ok, so you remember what
    I said about butterflies?

54:44.040 --> 54:44.980
      Harness their energy.

54:45.080 --> 54:45.980
             Mmmhmm.

54:46.080 --> 54:47.380
     And how do you do that?

54:47.480 --> 54:48.550
         Breathe it in.

54:48.650 --> 54:50.380
               Ok.

54:51.620 --> 54:56.920
         [Violin music]

54:57.020 --> 54:58.590
             Better?

54:58.690 --> 55:02.330
              Yeah.

55:02.430 --> 55:04.060
         You have worked
        so hard for this.

55:04.160 --> 55:07.400
      You be proud of that.

55:07.500 --> 55:11.040
  And most of all, go have fun
           out there.

55:11.140 --> 55:12.600
       Enjoy yourself, ok?

55:12.700 --> 55:14.200
               Ok.

55:19.540 --> 55:23.480
    Thanks for the pep talk,
              mom.

55:23.580 --> 55:25.020
   Ok, so let's get out there

55:25.120 --> 55:26.420
      before Hannah thinks
       you flew the coop.

55:26.520 --> 55:27.050
            [Laughs]

55:27.150 --> 55:28.720
               Ok.

55:32.860 --> 55:36.930
         [Violin music]

55:37.030 --> 55:40.600
           [Applause]

55:57.520 --> 55:59.620
   Don't think, just breathe.

55:59.720 --> 56:01.550
         Feel the music.

56:01.650 --> 56:03.090
            Feel it.

56:07.490 --> 56:09.830
        You can do this.

56:09.930 --> 56:12.130
  Next we have Sophia Daverston
          on the piano.

56:13.930 --> 56:23.070
           [Applause]

56:34.020 --> 56:47.360
         [Piano playing]

56:47.470 --> 57:00.340
         [Piano playing]

57:00.450 --> 57:13.320
         [Piano playing]

57:13.430 --> 57:26.340
         [Piano playing]

57:26.440 --> 57:39.350
         [Piano playing]

57:39.450 --> 57:52.400
         [Piano playing]

57:52.500 --> 57:59.100
         [Piano playing]

57:59.200 --> 58:06.740
         [Piano playing]

58:06.850 --> 58:17.490
           [Applause]

58:17.590 --> 58:24.930
           [Applause]

58:28.970 --> 58:31.100
       You were fantastic!

58:31.200 --> 58:33.240
  We will not know the judge's
   decision for another week,

58:33.340 --> 58:35.270
   but it's ok, you can relax.

58:35.370 --> 58:36.940
           Excuse me.

58:47.120 --> 58:53.590
            [sobbing]

59:05.200 --> 59:06.700
   And you're sure that it was
            a spider?

59:06.800 --> 59:08.640
       I know what I saw.

59:08.740 --> 59:10.140
   I'm going to get security.

59:23.320 --> 59:27.060
       What is it, honey?

59:27.160 --> 59:28.660
     It's probably nothing.

59:39.700 --> 59:40.870
       Thank you, Bethany.

59:51.380 --> 59:52.250
            Hey, mom.

59:52.350 --> 59:53.550
      I brought you lunch.

59:53.650 --> 59:54.650
       Thank you, Sophia.

59:54.750 --> 59:56.620
      Um, we need to talk.

59:56.720 --> 59:58.060
         Mom, I was just
        dropping it off.

59:58.160 --> 59:59.490
     It's just going to take
           one minute.

59:59.590 --> 01:00:00.560
             Please.

01:00:05.130 --> 01:00:07.330
    I just got off the phone
     with my friend Bethany

01:00:07.430 --> 01:00:08.670
      who lives in Marion.

01:00:08.770 --> 01:00:10.200
              And?

01:00:10.300 --> 01:00:13.740
      She's never heard of
        a Michelle Foley.

01:00:13.840 --> 01:00:15.610
             Really?

01:00:15.710 --> 01:00:17.670
      Maybe she registered
     under a different name.

01:00:17.780 --> 01:00:20.440
    Did she ever say anything
       to you about that?

01:00:20.550 --> 01:00:21.450
               No.

01:00:21.550 --> 01:00:23.150
     Well, Bethany suggested

01:00:23.250 --> 01:00:25.380
 that maybe she meant the public
      school, Marion High.

01:00:25.480 --> 01:00:26.420
   Mom, don't worry about it.

01:00:26.520 --> 01:00:29.290
           It's fine.

01:00:29.390 --> 01:00:30.550
         Ok, I know that
    she's your friend, honey.

01:00:30.660 --> 01:00:31.720
            I just...

01:00:31.820 --> 01:00:34.460
 I just want you to be careful.

01:00:34.560 --> 01:00:36.830
       You don't know who
       anybody really is,

01:00:36.930 --> 01:00:40.560
 and with everything that's been
   going on lately, it just...

01:00:40.670 --> 01:00:42.870
       I want you to keep
         an eye out, ok?

01:00:42.970 --> 01:00:44.200
           Sure, mom.

01:00:55.480 --> 01:00:56.680
         Michelle Foley.

01:00:56.780 --> 01:00:58.220
         I remember her.

01:00:58.320 --> 01:00:59.780
 Kind of quiet, kept to herself.

01:00:59.880 --> 01:01:01.420
       Not a bad student.

01:01:01.520 --> 01:01:03.290
 Decent grades, but the teachers
        used to complain

01:01:03.390 --> 01:01:06.520
      that she never really
        applied herself.

01:01:06.620 --> 01:01:07.860
     It must have been hard
    when she lost her mother.

01:01:07.960 --> 01:01:10.030
   I wouldn't know about that.

01:01:10.130 --> 01:01:11.500
 She said that's why she moved.

01:01:11.600 --> 01:01:14.900
      She wanted to be near
        her grandmother.

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:16.630
         She never said
      why she transferred?

01:01:16.730 --> 01:01:18.500
          Transferred?

01:01:18.600 --> 01:01:20.870
   She left about a month ago.

01:01:20.970 --> 01:01:23.010
     You didn't wonder why?

01:01:23.110 --> 01:01:26.510
    Michelle Foley graduated
         four years ago.

01:01:26.610 --> 01:01:28.210
         She graduated?

01:01:28.310 --> 01:01:29.710
      That's when she went
        to the hospital.

01:01:29.810 --> 01:01:31.350
            Hospital?

01:01:31.450 --> 01:01:33.550
        In Marion state.

01:01:33.650 --> 01:01:36.650
    She never mentioned that?

01:01:36.750 --> 01:01:37.690
               No.

01:01:37.790 --> 01:01:38.690
           She didn't.

01:01:38.790 --> 01:01:40.720
          [school bell]

01:01:40.830 --> 01:01:41.630
       Alright, everybody!

01:01:41.730 --> 01:01:43.130
       Get back to class!

01:02:09.690 --> 01:02:10.650
          [Door buzzes]

01:02:14.630 --> 01:02:15.630
          It's alright!

01:02:15.730 --> 01:02:17.990
            [Gasping]

01:02:28.070 --> 01:02:30.210
           Excuse me.

01:02:30.310 --> 01:02:32.080
     I have a few questions
      about Michelle Foley.

01:02:32.180 --> 01:02:34.380
     She was a patient here.

01:02:34.480 --> 01:02:36.980
       I'm sorry, patient
  information is confidential.

01:02:37.080 --> 01:02:39.080
  I'm not at liberty to discuss
         that with you.

01:02:39.180 --> 01:02:40.950
   But she was a patient here?

01:02:41.050 --> 01:02:42.320
              Miss.

01:02:42.420 --> 01:02:43.690
       Look, I don't need
        to know anything

01:02:43.790 --> 01:02:44.760
   about her medical history,
              but-

01:02:44.860 --> 01:02:45.890
        I'm sorry, miss.

01:02:45.990 --> 01:02:48.460
        I can't help you.

01:02:48.560 --> 01:02:49.560
    Thank you for your time.

01:03:58.800 --> 01:04:00.430
            She's 22.

01:04:19.120 --> 01:04:20.880
        Marion Rest Home.

01:04:20.990 --> 01:04:23.220
      Ellen Foley, please.

01:04:23.320 --> 01:04:24.860
      Uh,  sorry,  she  left
        four  months  ago.

01:04:24.960 --> 01:04:26.220
          Four months?

01:04:26.320 --> 01:04:28.160
          Do you have a
       forwarding address?

01:04:28.260 --> 01:04:31.360
          Can I ask what
        this is regarding?

01:04:31.460 --> 01:04:34.130
     Yes, my name is Angela,
      I work for Dr. Stein,

01:04:34.230 --> 01:04:36.130
 Ms. Foley's primary physician.

01:04:36.230 --> 01:04:37.930
     Our files show that she
     is overdue for renewal

01:04:38.040 --> 01:04:42.410
 on several of her prescriptions
   and no one's been in touch.

01:04:42.510 --> 01:04:46.440
   The last address we have on
  file was 784 Stoneward Court.

01:04:46.540 --> 01:04:47.680
      Thank you very much.

01:05:12.140 --> 01:05:13.340
        [Knocks on door]

01:05:38.660 --> 01:05:41.900
             [Gasps]

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:44.000
           Mrs. Foley!

01:05:44.100 --> 01:05:46.640
      I didn't know anyone
            was home.

01:05:46.740 --> 01:05:48.240
           I'm Sophia.

01:05:48.340 --> 01:05:49.340
      I don't know if she's
          mentioned me,

01:05:49.440 --> 01:05:51.040
 but I'm a friend of Michelle's.

01:05:57.380 --> 01:06:00.020
      Do you have any idea
      when she'll be home?

01:06:00.120 --> 01:06:02.020
           Mrs. Foley?

01:08:06.140 --> 01:08:07.240
    Can I make you something
             to eat?

01:08:07.340 --> 01:08:09.310
          Maybe later.

01:08:13.180 --> 01:08:14.520
              Hmm.

01:08:33.270 --> 01:08:37.670
    How often did your mother
             hit you?

01:08:37.779 --> 01:08:39.710
             Enough.

01:08:44.050 --> 01:08:45.380
     What about your father?

01:08:45.479 --> 01:08:47.020
        Did you know him?

01:08:53.020 --> 01:08:57.790
    How do you feel about him?

01:08:57.899 --> 01:09:02.200
         Angry, I guess.

01:09:02.300 --> 01:09:04.830
               Why?

01:09:04.939 --> 01:09:08.439
        Because he left.

01:09:08.540 --> 01:09:10.609
      He left me with her.

01:09:51.680 --> 01:09:53.850
         We need to talk
      about Lorraine Foley.

01:09:53.950 --> 01:09:55.290
  Where did you hear that name?

01:09:55.390 --> 01:09:56.190
     Did you know she died?

01:09:56.290 --> 01:09:57.220
               No.

01:09:57.320 --> 01:09:58.420
      She was an alcoholic.

01:09:58.520 --> 01:09:59.890
     I know she had issues.

01:09:59.990 --> 01:10:01.990
    That was a long time ago.

01:10:02.090 --> 01:10:03.790
  We had a brief relationship,

01:10:03.890 --> 01:10:06.000
  it was a couple years before
   your mother and I married.

01:10:06.100 --> 01:10:07.430
     Lorraine's mother lives
    right here in Ridgewood,

01:10:07.530 --> 01:10:09.030
       did you know that?

01:10:09.130 --> 01:10:10.970
               No.

01:10:11.070 --> 01:10:12.970
         She lives with
       her granddaughter.

01:10:13.070 --> 01:10:15.140
    Lorraine had a daughter?

01:10:15.240 --> 01:10:16.840
            Michelle.

01:10:20.510 --> 01:10:21.810
      Your friend Michelle?

01:10:21.910 --> 01:10:25.380
     Is Lorraine's daughter.

01:10:25.480 --> 01:10:26.780
      That's not possible.

01:10:28.550 --> 01:10:29.620
 We were done four years before.

01:10:29.720 --> 01:10:31.590
 Not if she lied about her age.

01:10:31.690 --> 01:10:34.490
 She's four years older than me.

01:10:34.590 --> 01:10:36.590
    She was institutionalized
     after her mother died.

01:10:36.690 --> 01:10:38.490
 Her grandmother is practically
          a vegetable.

01:10:42.270 --> 01:10:44.630
     You have to believe me.

01:10:44.740 --> 01:10:46.470
  All this time I had no idea.

01:10:50.570 --> 01:10:51.980
     You've gotta tell mom.

01:10:55.580 --> 01:10:57.080
      I know it's not easy,

01:10:57.180 --> 01:10:59.080
    but it's not fair keeping
         this from her.

01:10:59.180 --> 01:11:01.350
       She needs to know.

01:11:09.660 --> 01:11:12.360
      It was before we met.

01:11:12.460 --> 01:11:14.130
 I never knew she was pregnant.

01:11:14.230 --> 01:11:16.530
       I never even talked
          to her again.

01:11:29.080 --> 01:11:30.450
   We have to call the police.

01:11:30.550 --> 01:11:33.150
        Call the police?

01:11:33.250 --> 01:11:36.450
     Breaking and entering,
    destruction of property.

01:11:36.550 --> 01:11:39.090
     You think she's the one
  that broke into your office?

01:11:39.190 --> 01:11:42.590
   It can't be a coincidence.

01:11:42.690 --> 01:11:44.630
          Mom's right.

01:11:44.730 --> 01:11:46.030
    Michelle has been trying
      to get me in trouble

01:11:46.130 --> 01:11:47.860
    ever since she got here.

01:11:47.970 --> 01:11:51.530
    Sabotaging my schoolwork,
            my music.

01:11:51.640 --> 01:11:56.440
     She even took advantage
            of Alex.

01:11:56.540 --> 01:11:59.580
      I don't know how far
      she's willing to go.

01:12:03.580 --> 01:12:08.520
This detective gave me his card.

01:12:08.620 --> 01:12:11.390
      Fine, I'll call him.

01:12:18.330 --> 01:12:21.260
      Mom, he didn't know.

01:12:27.300 --> 01:12:29.270
 It doesn't make it any easier.

01:13:11.120 --> 01:13:24.430
         [Piano playing]

01:13:24.530 --> 01:13:29.970
         [Piano playing]

01:13:30.070 --> 01:13:37.540
         [Piano playing]

01:13:37.640 --> 01:13:40.740
         Michelle Foley!

01:13:40.840 --> 01:13:42.380
       [Knocking on door]

01:13:42.480 --> 01:13:45.150
        It's the police!

01:13:45.250 --> 01:13:52.660
        Are you in there?

01:13:52.760 --> 01:13:55.390
            [sobbing]
     I'm so sorry, grandma.

01:13:55.490 --> 01:13:57.630
      I have to leave you.

01:14:11.540 --> 01:14:12.480
              Hey!

01:14:12.580 --> 01:14:14.480
              Hey!

01:14:17.710 --> 01:14:31.030
         [Piano playing]

01:14:31.130 --> 01:14:39.170
         [Piano playing]

01:14:39.270 --> 01:14:40.340
      It's obvious Michelle
           hasn't been

01:14:40.440 --> 01:14:42.710
   in a healthy state of mind.

01:14:42.810 --> 01:14:44.740
     So all these incidents,
   they're connected with her?

01:14:44.840 --> 01:14:46.110
         It appears so.

01:14:46.210 --> 01:14:47.110
      Ok, so can you just-

01:14:47.210 --> 01:14:49.650
      how dangerous is she?

01:14:49.750 --> 01:14:52.780
   Even though she's unstable,
      her record is clean.

01:14:52.880 --> 01:14:55.650
   That being said, we're not
      taking this lightly.

01:14:55.750 --> 01:14:56.990
   For the next couple of days

01:14:57.090 --> 01:14:58.750
       we'll have a patrol
        car in the area.

01:14:58.860 --> 01:15:01.260
 We've notified your high school
     of the situation, too.

01:15:01.360 --> 01:15:02.990
           Thank you.

01:15:03.090 --> 01:15:04.330
  If she tries to make contact
           with you...

01:15:04.430 --> 01:15:06.700
    Yeah, you'll be the first
            to know.

01:15:06.800 --> 01:15:07.760
           Thank you.

01:15:07.870 --> 01:15:09.300
           Thank you.

01:15:41.930 --> 01:15:45.970
     Sophia got a letter from
   the Harold King Foundation.

01:15:46.070 --> 01:15:49.040
   Oh, I wonder what it says.

01:15:49.140 --> 01:15:51.610
     I should probably wait
           to open it.

01:15:51.710 --> 01:15:53.780
             Dylan?

01:15:53.880 --> 01:15:55.480
        Did you hear me?

01:16:05.760 --> 01:16:07.420
             [Gasps]

01:16:11.560 --> 01:16:12.700
               Hi.

01:16:12.800 --> 01:16:14.660
              Mom.

01:16:36.920 --> 01:16:38.350
       Hi, guys, I'm home!

01:16:54.570 --> 01:16:56.270
              Mom!

01:16:56.370 --> 01:16:58.740
   Did you see I got a letter
from the Harold King Foundation?

01:17:11.820 --> 01:17:13.890
     Hello? Is anyone here?

01:17:29.140 --> 01:17:35.080
      [Text message alert]

01:17:38.120 --> 01:17:39.720
           Oh my god.

01:17:39.820 --> 01:17:41.280
            Mom? Dad?

01:17:54.870 --> 01:17:57.100
        Congratulations.

01:17:57.200 --> 01:18:01.940
    You got your scholarship.

01:18:02.040 --> 01:18:04.440
         Where are they?

01:18:04.540 --> 01:18:06.780
     But I guess I shouldn't
      really be surprised.

01:18:06.880 --> 01:18:09.510
            Should I?

01:18:09.610 --> 01:18:13.280
   Things always seem to work
    out for you, don't they?

01:18:18.390 --> 01:18:23.530
      [sobbing] Ple- please
         don't hurt me.

01:18:23.630 --> 01:18:31.070
  You don't know what it's like
 to be abandoned by your father.

01:18:31.170 --> 01:18:34.970
   To watch your crazy mother
    drown herself in alcohol.

01:18:35.070 --> 01:18:36.540
       Whatever happened,
           I'm sorry.

01:18:36.640 --> 01:18:38.640
           I'm sorry.

01:18:38.740 --> 01:18:42.180
  After she died I had to find
 out what happened to my father

01:18:42.280 --> 01:18:46.480
     so I tracked him down.

01:18:48.720 --> 01:18:52.920
       Imagine my surprise
        when I found you.

01:18:53.020 --> 01:18:56.560
      The perfect daughter.

01:18:56.660 --> 01:18:59.260
     With the perfect house.

01:18:59.360 --> 01:19:01.860
       The perfect mother.

01:19:01.970 --> 01:19:02.970
        The perfect life.

01:19:03.070 --> 01:19:06.000
   The life I should have had.

01:19:06.100 --> 01:19:06.840
          It still can-

01:19:06.940 --> 01:19:11.370
        DON'T LIE TO ME!

01:19:11.480 --> 01:19:14.280
       I'm sorry, I forgot
     my breathing exercises.

01:19:14.380 --> 01:19:16.210
              Whew.

01:19:19.480 --> 01:19:23.020
   You know what they tell you
       in the institution?

01:19:23.120 --> 01:19:26.920
     That you have to accept
         what you have.

01:19:27.020 --> 01:19:31.590
   That you have to be content
     with what you're given.

01:19:31.700 --> 01:19:34.130
         That's my life.

01:19:34.230 --> 01:19:36.900
            But you.

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:38.300
      Why do you get to go
       to the nice school

01:19:38.400 --> 01:19:41.800
  with your little scholarship

01:19:41.910 --> 01:19:44.740
    while I just wither away
    in anger and resentment?

01:19:44.840 --> 01:19:46.240
          WHY?!!!!!!!!!

01:19:46.340 --> 01:19:48.210
 Hurting me, hurting our father,
           my mother,

01:19:48.310 --> 01:19:51.310
     it won't make your life
           any better!

01:19:51.410 --> 01:19:55.790
     You really haven't been
   paying attention, have you?

01:19:55.890 --> 01:19:59.090
      It's not about making
         my life better.

01:19:59.190 --> 01:20:01.660
        It's about making
          yours worse.

01:20:05.100 --> 01:20:06.330
           My parents.

01:20:06.430 --> 01:20:08.630
             Mmmhmm.

01:20:08.730 --> 01:20:13.200
    They need to be punished.

01:20:13.300 --> 01:20:15.340
      I won't let you hurt
           my family.

01:20:15.440 --> 01:20:17.570
       You can't stop me.

01:20:28.950 --> 01:20:30.920
           [Gunshots]

01:20:32.760 --> 01:20:38.860
           [Gunshots]

01:20:54.950 --> 01:20:56.780
   You're not gonna get away,
             Sophia!

01:20:59.080 --> 01:21:03.220
           [Gunshots]

01:21:20.040 --> 01:21:22.740
             Sophia.

01:21:22.840 --> 01:21:24.640
      Where are you going,
         little sister?

01:21:30.150 --> 01:21:35.080
           [Gunshots]

01:21:35.190 --> 01:21:36.920
             Dammit!

01:21:47.900 --> 01:21:49.400
            [Sobbing]

01:21:49.500 --> 01:21:59.210
            [Choking]

01:22:04.920 --> 01:22:12.720
            [Gasping]

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:24.870
           [Thumping]

01:22:31.270 --> 01:22:32.140
           Are you ok?

01:22:32.240 --> 01:22:32.910
         Yes, I'm fine.

01:22:33.010 --> 01:22:33.780
        Where's Michelle?

01:22:33.880 --> 01:22:34.680
          Where is she?

01:22:34.780 --> 01:22:36.250
       She's unconscious.

01:22:36.350 --> 01:22:39.380
      I called the police,
      they're on their way.

01:22:39.480 --> 01:22:41.380
    She won't be able to hurt
         anyone anymore.

01:22:41.480 --> 01:22:43.320
     I'm so glad you're ok.

01:22:45.420 --> 01:22:47.290
            Oh, baby.

01:22:47.390 --> 01:22:48.290
        I love you guys.

01:22:48.390 --> 01:22:50.330
       I love you so much.

01:22:58.600 --> 01:23:00.140
    There's still some room.

01:23:00.240 --> 01:23:02.170
        Get it in there.

01:23:02.270 --> 01:23:06.180
    Oh, that's officially it.

01:23:06.280 --> 01:23:08.610
  Little girl's off to college.

01:23:08.710 --> 01:23:11.150
       Guys, it's not like
     I'm never coming back.

01:23:11.250 --> 01:23:13.180
       Summer, Christmas.

01:23:13.280 --> 01:23:14.950
      There's Columbus Day,

01:23:15.050 --> 01:23:16.020
   there's President's Day...

01:23:16.120 --> 01:23:17.190
              Mom.

01:23:17.290 --> 01:23:18.820
          Don't worry.

01:23:18.920 --> 01:23:20.560
          I'll be fine.

01:23:20.660 --> 01:23:21.960
      Call us when you get
        to Carnegie Hall.

01:23:22.060 --> 01:23:22.590
           Come here.

01:23:22.690 --> 01:23:23.960
             I will.

01:23:24.060 --> 01:23:25.230
        I love you guys.

01:23:25.330 --> 01:23:26.260
           I love you.

01:23:28.300 --> 01:23:29.630
        I love you, too.

01:23:31.300 --> 01:23:32.270
           Drive safe.

01:23:32.370 --> 01:23:33.870
             I will.

